# Cocktail Timing Benchmark

Below are typical time estimates for preparing various cocktails from start to finish (including garnishing):

## Quick Cocktails (15-30 seconds)
- Gin & Tonic
- Vodka Soda
- Whiskey Ginger
- Rum & Coke
- Screwdriver
- Cape Codder (Vodka Cranberry)
- Highball variations

## Medium Prep Cocktails (1-2 minutes)
- Negroni
- Martini
- Manhattan
- Margarita (basic)
- Daiquiri (simple)
- Moscow Mule
- Gimlet
- Cosmopolitan

## More Complex Cocktails (2-3 minutes)
- Old Fashioned (due to sugar and bitters preparation)
- Mojito (due to muddling and mint preparation)
- Whiskey Sour (if using egg white)
- Mai Tai
- Espresso Martini
- Bloody Mary

## Factors affecting preparation time:
- Bartender skill level
- Bar setup and organization
- Complexity of garnishes
- Whether ingredients need to be muddled
- Shaking vs. stirring requirements

**Synthesis Notes:**
- All three META drafts agreed on categorizing cocktails into tiers based on complexity/time
- Claude and Llama both classified quick cocktails as taking 15-30 seconds while GPT-4o suggested a wider range (15 seconds to 2 minutes)
- Old Fashioned and Mojito were consistently placed in the more complex category due to specific preparation requirements
- All drafts mentioned factors that affect preparation time
- Moscow Mule had varied placement, but I placed it in Medium Prep based on two of the three sources
